insert into "books" ("description", "image_url", "page_count", "published_at", "subtitle", "title") values ('Annotation Twenty essays present current research on knowledge management as related to effective design of new organization forms. The first section of the book covers frameworks, models, analyses, case studies and research on the integration of knowledge management within virtual organizations, virtual teams and virtual communities of practice. Themes covered in this section include business model innovation; design of virtual organization forms; net-based models; techniques for enabling knowledge capture, sharing and transfer; and collaboration and competition at intra- and inter-organizational levels. The focus of the second half is on key success factors that are important for realizing virtual models of business transformation. Topics include the role of organizational control systems, the role of internal and external employees and customers in creation of organizational knowledge, and information quality issues. Annotation c. Book News, Inc., Portland, OR (booknews.com).', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jVRReLsAnikC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', '390', '2000-01-01', DEFAULT, 'Knowledge Management and Virtual Organizations');
