insert into "books" ("description", "image_url", "page_count", "published_at", "subtitle", "title") values ('The Gestalt approach is particularly known for its broad spectrum of therapeutic interventions, including artistic materials and methods from the fine and performing arts. Creativity is a significant criterion for health, well-being and intelligence. It reflects the ability to find new solutions and promotes the flexibility required to adjust productively during critical life events. Gestalt therapy employs the term "creative adjustment” to emphasize the importance of this ability for personal and professional growth. The book focuses on the fruitful interchange between theoretical guidelines and professional practice. A strong emphasis lies on the historical and philosophical foundations of this topic, on clinical practice and case studies, and on various fields of applications (neuroscience, developmental psychology). A solid representation of American and European theoreticians bridges a divide between continents and reflects the productive discourse amoung schools and "streams” of Gestalt therapy.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sb1JMWHxbyUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', '312', '2003-09-01', 'The Art of Gestalt Therapy', 'Creative License');
