insert into "books" ("description", "image_url", "page_count", "published_at", "subtitle", "title") values ('Dreams don’t come true, but nightmares do. When Zeke Garrett is reactivated to mentor the next dreamer that pops up on the Somnium’s radar, he’s sure it’s a mistake. The covert organization is still struggling to conceal the fallout from his last assignment, a fatal catastrophe. From the first blast of her pepper spray, he realizes this neonati, whose nightmares manifest vampires straight from the pages of pop-culture, is more than he bargained for—a potential dreamwalker. But before her training can begin, he has to convince the stubborn, mouthy woman she’s not dreaming. Maggie Mackey hasn’t slept well in a month, but that doesn’t explain how the monsters from her nightmares suddenly seem so real. Or why, when a team of intimidating, sword-wielding toughs rescue her, their leader captures her mouth in a swift, knee-weakening kiss. Once he tears himself away, Zeke’s mental forehead smacking begins. Their embrace has confirmed they have a rare tangible bond, a phenomenon which fooled him once before. Somehow he must tutor the woman of his dreams without getting attached. Otherwise her nightmares could become his own. Warning: Contains lots of cussing, pop culture references and monsters with nasty, big, pointy teeth.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Vfjvhs1YgecC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', '135', '2013-05-28', DEFAULT, 'Tangible');
